{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"aa491bd7-0981-47b4-9442-a6b5adcbbffa","content":"The project doesn't exist yet in this workspace, but here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a **dotnet tool** on NuGet.org:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n\n  <!-- Makes it a dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server using stdio transport.</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** — marks the project as a .NET tool (must be a console app).\n- **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command users type after installing.\n- **Stdio transport** works naturally with dotnet tools since the tool runs as a process.\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install --global MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # runs via stdio\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8ff0938b-7517-44f1-ab70-5913653c6e4a","outputTokens":464,"requestId":"7013:33DFCD:149E41F:17D6024:69EC11E8"},"id":"cfe15464-38ec-4bf3-a1b4-efdd0a18bf89","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:59:29.490Z","parentId":"39e07e84-8189-410c-8b79-145cd0a9630a"}
